[1mStructure follows the RECIPE-GUIDE.md template:[22m[0m[0m
- **The Problem:** Vivid ICU scenario establishing why mortality prediction matters for resource allocation, goals-of-care conversations, and clinical decision-making. Covers limitations of traditional severity scores (APACHE, SOFA, SAPS).[0m[0m
- **The Technology:** Deep dive into why this is hard (high-frequency multivariate time series, treatment confounding, self-fulfilling prophecy, calibration across subgroups), ML approaches (RNNs, TCNs, transformers, gradient-boosted trees, survival models), feature engineering for ICU data, calibration requirements, and the self-fulfilling prophecy problem with mitigations.[0m[0m
- **General Architecture Pattern:** Vendor-agnostic pipeline from data ingestion through feature store, inference, calibration, clinical display, and outcome tracking/retraining.[0m[0m
